Write a script to accept two integers (Use html formhaving2 textboxes). Write a PHP script to,

a. Find mod of the two numbers. b. Find the power of first number raised to the second. c. Find the sum of first n numbers (considering first numbers n) d. Find the factorial of second number. (Write separate function for each of the above operations.)


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Integer Operations</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Enter Two Integers</h2>
<form method="post">
    First Number: <input type="number" name="num1" required><br><br>
    Second Number: <input type="number" name="num2" required><br><br>
    <input type="submit" name="submit" value="Calculate">
</form>

<?php
if(isset($_POST['submit'])) {
    $num1 = intval($_POST['num1']);
    $num2 = intval($_POST['num2']);

    echo "<h3>Entered Numbers: $num1 and $num2</h3>";

    // a) Modulus
    function find_mod($a, $b) {
        return $a % $b;
    }
    echo "a) Modulus ($num1 % $num2) = " . find_mod($num1, $num2) . "<br>";

    // b) Power
    function find_power($a, $b) {
        return pow($a, $b);
    }
    echo "b) Power ($num1 ^ $num2) = " . find_power($num1, $num2) . "<br>";

    // c) Sum of first n numbers (first number n)
    function sum_first_n($n) {
        $sum = 0;
        for($i=1; $i<=$n; $i++) {
            $sum += $i;
        }
        return $sum;
    }
    echo "c) Sum of first $num1 numbers = " . sum_first_n($num1) . "<br>";

    // d) Factorial of second number
    function factorial($n) {
        if($n < 0) return "Undefined";
        $fact = 1;
        for($i=1; $i<=$n; $i++) {
            $fact *= $i;
        }
        return $fact;
    }
    echo "d) Factorial of $num2 = " . factorial($num2) . "<br>";
}
?>

</body>
</html>


Que.2.Download iris data set file. Read this csv file using read_csv () function. Take samples from entire dataset. Display maximum and minimum values of all numeric attributes


import pandas as pd

# 1. Read Iris dataset
# Make sure iris.csv is downloaded and in the same folder
iris = pd.read_csv("iris.csv")

print("----- First 5 rows of the dataset -----")
print(iris.head())

# 2. Take a random sample (say 10 rows)
sample_data = iris.sample(n=10, random_state=42)  # random_state for reproducibility
print("\n----- Sampled 10 rows -----")
print(sample_data)

# 3. Display maximum and minimum values of all numeric attributes
# Assuming numeric attributes are the first 4 columns in Iris dataset
numeric_cols = iris.select_dtypes(include='number').columns

print("\n----- Maximum values of numeric attributes -----")
print(sample_data[numeric_cols].max())

print("\n----- Minimum values of numeric attributes -----")
print(sample_data[numeric_cols].min()).
